cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving the performance of Recursive Neural Networks (RecNN) for natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a hypernetwork to generate semantic composition parameters dynamically, which involves learning the parameters of a neural network, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new model architecture, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments involve classification tasks, which could also suggest cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) as possible categories.
